The paper deals with problems related to geometric graphs and spanners, which are typical topics in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of chromatic number and coloring techniques suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also involves the analysis of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), as well as graph theory (cs.GT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA) in the context of geometric graphs.
